  aemeasurable := sorry
```

The goal is `AEMeasurable (fun ω => u \ X ω) P`.
We have `hX : IsBernoulliOn X u p P`.
`IsBernoulliOn X u p P` is defined as `HasLaw X Ber(u, p) P`.
From `HasLaw X Ber(u, p) P`, we can extract that `X` is `AEMeasurable`.
Specifically, `HasLaw X μ P` implies `AEMeasurable X P`.
So we have `AEMeasurable X P`.
The complement of an `AEMeasurable` set is also `AEMeasurable`.
Therefore, `AEMeasurable (fun ω => u \ X ω) P`.

